Class ProblemValidators

java.lang.Object
  sndlib.core.validation.ProblemValidators

ProblemValidator
public class ProblemValidators
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProblemValidator

This class provides the common method to check a given Problem for feasibility.

It aggregates all problem validators which are currently implemented.

Roman Klaehne

Field Detail

MODEL

public static final ProblemValidator MODEL
This validator checks whether the model combination in a network design problem is supported in SNDlib.

Actually a valid model combination (Model) must satisfy the following conditions:
  • SurvivabilityModel == ONE_PLUS_ONE_PROTECTION => RoutingModel == SINGLE_PATH
  • LinkModel == UNDIRECTED <=> DemandModel == UNDIRECTED
  • LinkModel != UNDIRECTED <=> Demand == DIRECTED

The following models are not yet supported in SNDlib:
  • RoutingModel OSPF_EQUAL_COST_MULTI_PATH
  • RoutingModel OSPF_SINGLE_PATH
  • NodeModel NODE_HARDWARE

See Also:
Model

ADMISSIBLE_PATHS_FEASIBILITY

public static final ProblemValidator ADMISSIBLE_PATHS_FEASIBILITY
If the admissible path model of a network design problem is set to EXPLICIT_LIST this validator checks whether the admissible paths of all demands in a given network are feasible. An admissible path is feasible if it connects the end nodes of the demand. With an undirected demand model, the path may be defined from target to source of the demand, otherwise it must be directed from source to target.

The direction into which the links can be traversed is determined by the link model.

If the admissible path model is not EXPLICIT_LIST this validator has no effect.

See Also:
AdmissiblePathModel, AdmissiblePath

ADMISSIBLE_PATHS_EXISTENCE

public static final ProblemValidator ADMISSIBLE_PATHS_EXISTENCE
If the admissible path model is set to EXPLICIT_LIST this validator checks at least one admissible path is specified for each demand in the network.

If the admissible path model is not EXPLICIT_LIST this validator has no effect.

See Also:
AdmissiblePathModel, AdmissiblePath

DEMAND_VALUES

public static final ProblemValidator DEMAND_VALUES
In case of an INTEGER routing model this validator checks whether the values of all demands in a given network are integral.

If the routing model is not INTEGER this validator has no effect.

See Also:
RoutingModel, Demand

ALL

public static final ProblemValidator ALL
